<taxonomicName authority="Walsingham, 1907" authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1907" box="[550,595,837,860]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Hypatopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="143" pageNumber="144" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vitis">
<emphasis box="[550,595,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="143" pageNumber="144">vitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from Latin meaning, a centurion's staff made of a branch of a vine.
</paragraph>
